review_blob: nice beer. kinda piney in aroma, and appearance is somewhat cloudy, but normal for this style. great flavor and overall nice palate. try this one for sure.
nice amber color with pleasant aroma.strong flavor, citrusey and toasty. not great aftertaste. overall decent beer.
nice color with a great head. somewhat skunky, but with a tangy bite that reminds me of blueberries. watery aftertaste. overall rather good beer.
very dark in color with a decent head. cloves and molasses present in aroma. roasted malts with several christmas flavors. clove aftertaste. decent, but not great overall.
very light color with a nice wheat aroma, like a fresh loaf of bread. hints of citrus in aroma. taste, however, does not match up well with aroma. very hoppy with sub-par aftertaste.
barley and malt present in aroma. pleasant toasty taste with mild aftertaste. overall good beer.
strong roasted barley aroma. strong malt flavors, reminds me of coffee with a pleasant aftertaste. overall decent beer.
great beer! pleasant head and aroma. grea head with wonderful flavors. smooth, pleasant aftertaste.
great color with nice head. decent aroma with hints of citrus. nice bitter/sweet taste with a decetn aftertaste. consistency is a little watery, however.
rather skunky aroma with a greenish tint. extremely bitter first taste with an unbalanced flavor. leaves an oily aftertaste.
not a fan of this beer at all. rathe upleasant aroma, and the appearance lacks appeal.
nice beer with a nice malt aroma. head dissipates fast. nice malty flavor with low bitterness. overall not bad for a heine.
not a bad beer, but not a great beer in my opinion. somewhat bitter aroma and dark appearance that reminds me of apple cider. mild hops with a decent bitterness, but somewhat watery consistency.
no head with a very poor appearance. fruity aroma is the only enjoyable part of this beer as it has a rather bland taste and unenjoyable aftertaste. not a good beer.
very nice beer. great color wih a reat head. very enjoyable aroma with a remarkable flavor. nice clean finish leaves you wanting more.
rather light color, with a distinct aroma that reminds me of a fresh loaf of bread. decent hops flavor that had hints of yeast in it. overall, flavor was not what I expected from the aroma.
decent color with a nice head. a tad hazy, however. very noticable yeast aroma with a yeasty flavor that masks the hops somewhat. leaves an oily palate.
very light in color, holds a decent head. decent aroma, but a surprisingly well balanced flavor overall.
rather watery looking beer with a very weak head. rather watered down hops aroma, with a rather yeasty smell. very watery taste.
nice amber colored beer, pours a decent head. pleasant malt aroma. moderate hops in the flavor lends itself well to a nice malt taste. decent palate.
one of my top ten; very light and clear, this beer pours well and leaves a decent head. unique aroma (somewhat citrusey) with a mild hops flavor and a hint of lemon. very well balanced beer.
rather nice beer. great color with a great head. nice bitter aroma. very well balanced flavor with a spicy aftertaste, leaving a clean palate.
very dark beer that pours with a weak head. aroma has hints of strong malts. palate tastes a little unbalanced with a rather oily consistency.
decent beer, but not great. hints of fermented yeast and molasses in the aroma. burnt malt flavor with a bitter aftertaste. thicker consistency than what Im used to.
